# =============================================================================
# .gitleaksignore — suppress confirmed false-positives by unique fingerprint
#
# WHEN TO ADD A FINGERPRINT HERE:
#   Only when the finding is a known fake/test value that cannot be fixed with
#   #gitleaks:allow (e.g., it is inside a committed diff you cannot rewrite).
#
# HOW TO GET FINGERPRINTS:
#   gitleaks git --report-format json --report-path /tmp/r.json
#   jq -r '.[] | "\(.Fingerprint)  # \(.RuleID) — \(.File):\(.StartLine)"' /tmp/r.json
#
# FINGERPRINT FORMATS:
#   dir scan → <file>:<ruleID>:<line>
#   git scan → <commitSHA>:<file>:<ruleID>:<line>
# =============================================================================

